Third-party code

The compiled `pyfastmm._fastmm_ext` extension is built from the FaSTMM2
(Fast Superposition T-Matrix Method) Fortran source, vendored as a git
submodule under external/fastmm2/
(https://bitbucket.org/planetarysystemresearch/fastmm2) and included in
patched form under src/pyfastmm/_fortran/patches/ (a pure ASCII
transliteration of a few UTF-8 math symbols in comments, needed to make
the source parseable by numpy.f2py -- no algorithm or runtime behavior
change). That source is used under its own licenses, all permissive:

